comments.body:
Checked into this further and the abrtd service has a list of keys that it checks for in the file {code}/etc/abrt/gpg_keys{code}

Since our release key is not listed in the file an error is emitted stating that the package is not properly signed.

This error message can be ignored, but you should be able to make it go away by adding the key file {code}/etc/pki/rpm-gpg/eucalyptus-release.pub{code} to the list of keys in {code}/etc/abrt/gpg_keys{code} and restarting the abrtd service.
